  title: How can you use the ternary conditional operator to assign a value based
    on a condition?
  text: 'You can use the ternary operator to assign a value to a variable depending
    on the result of a condition.

    ##REF##code,

    string state = health >
    0 ? "ALIVE" : "DEAD";

    ##REF##

    If health is above 0 then state will
    be "ALIVE", if not it will be "DEAD".'
